ObAgent: uncertain

Many inter-service and some self trace durations rose (p95/mean), indicating overall increased RPC/processing latency, but this pattern can be caused by either network delays or host/container CPU contention. To disambiguate, check:
- container CPU usage and node CPU metrics with whether_is_abnormal_metric (to detect CPU load/spikes);
- container network metrics (packet retransmits, packet loss, interface errors, and network latency) with whether_is_abnormal_metric;
- or run a collect_trace/span breakdown to see whether time is spent in network wait vs in-service processing.
JudgeAgent: No - The agents identified strong evidence (node-1 system.net.tcp.retrans_segs anomaly sev~55.7, elevated container network receive MB on node-5, and multiple gRPC latency trace spikes at 13:03/13:10/13:12/13:15/13:19) but did not pick a single root-location from the candidate list, reported inconsistent granularity (node-level metric vs container-level fault type), and failed to pin one exact occurrence datetime. Therefore the root cause is not fully and consistently specified.

